Package game

  • Interface Summary
    Interface Description
    Behaviour
    A factory for creating actions.
    ComputeDistance
    Provides logic to compute layer distance (how many steps an Actor needs to take to get there) between 2 locations, assuming there is no obstacles in between.
    Visitable
    Declares the accept operation.
    Visitor<T>
    Declare the visit operations for all the types of visitable classes.
  • Class Summary
    Class Description
    Application
    The main operational logic of the game.
    BuyAction
    Represents the Player's interaction with the VendingMachine.
    DinosaurMap
    Represents the map that the Player is interacting with.
    GameLocation
    Represents a Location in the map.
    GameLocation.GameLocationIterator
    An Iterator over the Location from nearest to farthest from the current Location.
    GameWorld
    The world that all the maps are in, represents the virtual world that we are interacting with.
    Player
    The Player of the game.
    QuitAction
    Quits the game, by removing the Player from the map he is standing on.
    SearchItemAction
    Player searches for Item from within the SearchableGround.
    ShootAction
    Handles ranged weapon shooting action/logic, performed exclusively by Player.
  • Enum Summary
    Enum Description
    ActorCapability
    Added to Actors for categorisation.
    GroundCapability
    Added to Grounds for categorisation.
    ItemCapability
    Added to Items for categorisation.
